msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/alias1"
msgid "player"
msgstr "jugador"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/alias2"
msgid "AI"
msgstr "IA"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/alias3"
msgid "ger"
msgstr "ale"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/convoy"
msgid "Enemy Convoy arrival scheduled for:"
msgstr "Llegada de convoy enemigo programada para el:"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/date"
msgid "9th of November, 1941 · Tikhvin railway hub"
msgstr "9 de noviembre de 1941 · Centro ferroviario de Tikhvin"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/location"
msgid "Tikhvin railway hub. 9th of November."
msgstr "Centro ferroviario de Tikhvin. 9 de noviembre."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/name"
msgid "The Cold Supper"
msgstr "La cena fría"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/name_big"
msgid "The Cold Supper"
msgstr "La cena fría"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"Tikhvin was as far east as ‘army group north’ would ever get. The Soviet "
"counter- attack of December 41 pushed \n"
"the Germans out almost exactly one month after it had been lost. Once re- "
"taken, the Soviets never lost control of \n"
"the Tikhvin railway hub again and Leningrad would not fall, despite the fact "
"that the siege lasted almost 900 days. "
msgstr "Tikhvin se encontraba lo más lejos que podía ubicarse al este. El contrataque soviético ocurrido en diciembre de 1941 expulsó a \nlos alemanes exactamente un mes después de perderlo. Cuando retomaron el control del centro ferroviario de Tikhvin fue para siempre, \ny Leningrado no pereció pese a los 900 días que duró el asedio. "

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"Because you lost the battle, the people of Leningrad will receive even "
"smaller rations than they already did until now. \n"
"The situation has just become critical! There is no way of saying how many "
"people will pay the highest price for this failure."
msgstr "Has perdido la batalla, por lo que el pueblo de Leningrado recibirá raciones aun más pequeñas. \nLa situación es insostenible, un incontable número de personas va a pagar por esto."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/place"
msgid "Special Detachment"
msgstr "Destacamento especial"

#, boost-format
msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/progress_p3"
msgid ""
"Compromise the Garrison! %1% Out of a minimum of 4 targets accomplished."
msgstr "¡Asusta a la guarnición! %1% objetivos de 4 completados."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/01"
msgid ""
"Night time reduces units' vision but vehicles and loud gun shots will be "
"heard over distance. Try to be stealthy."
msgstr "La visión nocturna reduce la visión de las unidades, sin embargo, los vehículos y disparos se escuchan a cierta distancia. Intenta no hacer ruido."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/02"
msgid ""
"Look for something to contaminate the fuel tank. Get a soldier to bring the "
"item close to the hatch."
msgstr "Busca algo con lo que contaminar el depósito de combustible. Pídele a un soldado que acerque el objeto a la escotilla."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/03"
msgid ""
"To contaminate the enemy kitchen, take a soldier with a repair kit in his "
"hands and bring it to the kitchen area. Engine lubricants are not "
"particularily edible."
msgstr "Para contaminar la cocina enemiga, controla un soldado que lleve un kit de reparación y llévalo a la cocina. El lubricante en concreto no es comestible."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/04"
msgid ""
"To take out the German howitzers silently, bring a soldier close enough to "
"the gun barrel and he will sabotage the gun."
msgstr "Para acabar con los obuses alemanes en silencio acerca un soldado al cañón del arma para que la sabotee."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/05"
msgid ""
"There are several paths leading to the second aerosled. Scouting will be "
"needed to determine the best one."
msgstr "Hay varios caminos que llevan al segundo aerosani. Explóralos para determinar cuál es el más adecuado."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/06"
msgid ""
"Try to remain stealthy. Do not get too close to sleeping germans or raise "
"suspicion. You should use the silenced Nagant pistol to take out enemies "
"quietly."
msgstr "Trata de avanzar en sigilo. No te acerques demasiado al personal alemán que está durmiendo para no levantar sospechas. Para acabar con los enemigos sin hacer ruido, usa la Nagant silenciada."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/07"
msgid ""
"A high ranking officer is performing an inspection. He may carry documents. "
"You must wait for the right time to ambush him."
msgstr "Hay un oficial de rango superior realizando una inspección. Puede que lleve algunos documentos, espera al momento indicado para atacar."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/08"
msgid "The target may be eliminated silently. Come closer for instructions."
msgstr "Es posible eliminar al objetivo en silencio. Acércate para saber más."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_assistant/09"
msgid ""
"There is a fuel supply area which we should sabotage. Quietly, if "
"possible... I have some ideas."
msgstr "Hay una zona de reabastecimiento de combustible que nos conviene sabotear. En silencio, si es posible... Creo que sé cómo."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/01"
msgid "Full throttle! He's right behind us!"
msgstr "¡Pisa a fondo! ¡Está detrás!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/02"
msgid "Left!"
msgstr "¡Izquierda!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/03"
msgid "Go through the shrubs! He won't know where we went!"
msgstr "¡Atraviesa los matorrales! ¡No sabrás dónde estamos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/04"
msgid ""
"We have to regroup with the other aerosled! .... the radio caught a bullet, "
"we can't communicate ... we will have to find them in another way!"
msgstr "¡Tenemos que reagruparnos con el resto de aerosanis! ... La radio ha sido alcanzada por un disparo, no podemos comunicarnos... ¡Habrá que buscar la forma de encontrarlos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/05"
msgid "We have the Documents! Let me see..."
msgstr "¡Tenemos los documentos! Veamos..."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/06"
msgid ""
"A Panzer got on our tail and we had to evade using a different route, but "
"our radio was broken... what's the status?"
msgstr "Un Panzer se nos colocó al rebufo y tuvimos que cambiar de ruta, pero se nos ha estropeado la radio... ¿Cuál es el estado?"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/07"
msgid ""
"Abort? No! We must take action now while they are resting. First, we must "
"find out where their depots and supplies are, and destroy them."
msgstr "¿Abortar? ¡No! Tenemos que actuar ahora que están descansando. Primero vamos a averiguar la ubicación de los suministros y depósitos para después destruirlos."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/08"
msgid "I can translate German... sounds like a cunning plan... Let's go."
msgstr "Sé hablar alemán... Parece un plan astuto... Vamos."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/09"
msgid ""
"Hmm. It seems we laid our hands on the complete plan of the defence sectors "
"and units located here, plus the scheduled arrival of new logistic columns. "
"This is pure gold, Comrades."
msgstr "Mmm, parece que tenemos entre manos el plan completo de los sectores y unidades defensivas de la zona junto a la llegada de las nuevas columnas logísticas. Hemos encontrado oro, camaradas."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/10"
msgid ""
"We will wreak all sorts of havoc while we can! We could potentially "
"visit.... let's see... An artillery position! The Barracks! The fuel "
"depot... "
msgstr "¡Vamos a sembrar el pánico mientras podamos! Veamos, qué podemos visitar... Ah, ¡un puesto de artillería! ¡Los barracones! El depósito de combustible... "

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/11"
msgid ""
"Apparently, judging by the distance between German units, they rely on a "
"powerful radio vehicle for communication. If we can take that out, the "
"Germans here will be isolated. Look for antennas to find it..."
msgstr "Parece que, a juzgar por la distancia existente entre las unidades alemanas, cuentan con un vehículo que incorpora una radio potente de comunicación. Sin ella, los alemanes quedarán desamparados. Busca las antenas para encontrarla..."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/12"
msgid ""
"Don't let us get spotted or noticed by enemy officers! Make sure to shoot "
"them before engaging into combat. They will likely call for reinforcements!"
msgstr "¡No dejes que nos encuentren los oficiales enemigos! Dispáralos antes de que te descubran, ¡si no solicitarán refuerzos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/13"
msgid ""
"That officer over there is still safe and sound! I bet he's calling "
"reinforcements as we speak. Brace yourselves!"
msgstr "¡Aquel oficial de allí sigue sano y salvo! Seguro que está solicitando refuerzos, ¡resistid!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/14"
msgid ""
"See that guy with the peaked cap? He's an officer! You should have taken him "
"out by now! I bet he is calling in reinforcements."
msgstr "¿Ves a aquel con la gorra de visera? ¡Pues es un oficial! Tendrías que haberlo abatido... Seguro que está solicitando refuerzos."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/15"
msgid ""
"Bloody hell, this place stinks of petrol. The fuel must have an open valve "
"somewhere. Hmmm.... We could put some chemicals into the fuel to stall their "
"engines... "
msgstr "Maldita sea, este sitio apesta a petróleo. Debe ser que se han dejado una válvula abierta. Mmmm... Podríamos echar productos químicos en el combustible para chafarles los motores... "

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/16"
msgid ""
"I'm sure we don't want to interrupt their sleep... What a great occassion. "
"Why don't we introduce a new ingredient onto the kitchen ovens? Erm... go "
"fetch a repair kit. I'm sure there's some delicious lubricants and anti-"
"freezing fluids in there. "
msgstr "No creo que queramos interrumpirles el sueño... Es una buena oportunidad. ¿Por qué no metemos algún ingrediente en los hornos de la cocina? Mmm... Trae un kit de reparación. Creo que los líquidos lubricante y anticongelante le darían un toque delicioso. "

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/17"
msgid ""
"Aha, there's the artillery. I suspect if we blow them up, the noise will "
"alert the fascists. How about we take out the guards silently... and then we "
"put some pebbles in the gun barrels? Next time they fire... they will have "
"some surprise fireworks!"
msgstr "Ajá, ahí está la artillería. Intuyo que, si la explotamos, el ruido alertará a los fascistas. ¿Y si nos cargamos a los guardias en silencio y luego colocamos piedrecitas en los cañones? Así, la próxima vez que disparen, ¡recibirán una fiesta de fuegos artificiales!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/18"
msgid ""
"Comrades, in a few minutes a fuel convoy is scheduled to arrive. We should "
"take it out!"
msgstr "Camaradas, faltan unos minutos para que llegue el convoy con combustible. ¡Démosle duro!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/19"
msgid ""
"A logistics column is scheduled to arrive in a few minutes. The Manifest: "
"Howitzer ammunition. I don't think we should let the fascist dogs have any "
"of that!"
msgstr "Faltan unos minutos para que llegue una columna de logística. Lo evidente: la munición del obús. ¡Lo mejor será que esos chuchos fascistas ni se acerquen!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/20"
msgid "Oh yes. Guten Appetit, swines!"
msgstr "Ah, sí. ¡Guten appetit, cerdos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/21"
msgid "Alright Comrades. That's enough. Time to get the hell out!"
msgstr "De acuerdo, camaradas. Ya basta. ¡Salgamos cagando leches!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/22"
msgid "Hah! They won't know what hit 'em. "
msgstr "¡Ja, ja! No van a saber ni de dónde les viene. "

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/23"
msgid "That's the howitzers! Good job."
msgstr "¡Los obuses! Buen trabajo."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/24"
msgid ""
"Excellent. They can't call for reinforcements now.  But this is no license "
"to go out there with guns blazing! They still outnumber us and we should try "
"and act quietly!"
msgstr "Genial, ya no pueden solicitar refuerzos. Eso sí, ¡eso no significa que podamos ir dando el cante con cañonazos! Nos superan en número, así que ¡tenemos que actuar cuanto antes!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/25"
msgid ""
"The officer by the roadblock might be calling in reinorcements, kill him "
"right now!"
msgstr "El oficial de la barricada quizá esté solicitando refuerzos, ¡acaba con él!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/26"
msgid "I bet that officer just called for reinforcements!"
msgstr "¡Seguro que el oficial acaba de solicitar refuerzos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/27"
msgid "That officer by the sandbags will have called in reinforcements by now!"
msgstr "¡El oficial junto a los sacos de arena seguramente haya solicitado refuerzos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/28"
msgid "Officer spotted! Don't let him detect you!"
msgstr "¡Oficial avistado! ¡Que no te vea!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/29"
msgid ""
"Officer! Don't get into a fight without killing him first, or else he might "
"call reinforcements."
msgstr "¡Oficial! No llames la atención sin abatirlo antes para que no solicite refuerzos."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/30"
msgid ""
"Damn! We woke them up! I guess the only way to sabotage this place now is to "
"kill everybody."
msgstr "¡Mierda! ¡Los hemos despertado! Me parece que la única alternativa es acabar con todos."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/arty"
msgid ""
"There is an artillery battery which we must take care of. I got an idea for "
"taking them out silently when we get there."
msgstr "Hay una batería de artillería de la que nos deberíamos ocupar. Tengo una idea para hacerlo de forma sigilosa."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/barracks"
msgid ""
"The Fascists have some designated barracks. I'm sure we could stealthily "
"deal with them while they sleep."
msgstr "Los fascistas disponen de unos barracones designados. Deberíamos lidiar con ellos mientras duermen."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_officer/fuel"
msgid ""
"There is a fuel supply area which we should sabotage. Quietly, if "
"possible... I have some ideas."
msgstr "Hay una zona de reabastecimiento de combustible que nos conviene sabotear. En silencio, si es posible... Creo que sé cómo."

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_partisan/01"
msgid "Comrades! Thanks for helping us! Let us help you on your mission!"
msgstr "¡Camaradas, gracias por la ayuda! ¡Os echaremos una mano con la misión!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_partisan/02"
msgid "Kill the fascists!"
msgstr "¡Abatid a los fascistas!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_radioman/01"
msgid ""
"Comrade Commissar! We thought you were dead! We have been unable to contact "
"you since we approached Tikhvin!"
msgstr "¡Comisario, pensábamos que habías muerto! ¡Llevamos sin poder contactar contigo desde que nos acercamos a Tikhvin!"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_radioman/02"
msgid ""
"Not good Sir... It's full of germans building defences. It's suicidal to "
"attack the enemy garrison. Should we abort?"
msgstr "No pinta bien, señor... Hay demasiados alemanes protegiendo la guarnición, sería un suicidio. ¿Abortamos misión?"

msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_radioman/03"
msgid "How shall we proceed, Comrade Commissar?"
msgstr "¿Cómo procedemos, comisario?"

#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
msgctxt "mission/single/01-rus/1941_12_tikhvin/speech/narrator_radioman/04"
msgid ""
msgstr ""
"Project-Id-Version: \n"
"POT-Creation-Date: \n"
"PO-Revision-Date: \n"
